        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName><name ref="Ursus de Petro Groso">Urso de Petro
                            Gr[o]so</name></persName> de <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        posita [i]n [...]ia <geogName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Books #Rent_in_money #Penalty #Fundi #Landed_possessions #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fisheries #Cereals #Hay/fodder #Wine"
                            ref="#estates/3936"><placeName
                                key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Books #Rent_in_money #Penalty #Fundi #Landed_possessions #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fisheries #Cereals #Hay/fodder #Wine"
                                >[Ca]pralia</placeName></geogName>, <rs
                            key="#Massae #Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi #Landed_possessions #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fisheries #Cereals #Hay/fodder #Wine"
                            >mass[a]</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Massae #Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi #Landed_possessions #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Fisheries #Cereals #Hay/fodder #Wine"
                            ref="#estates/2479"><placeName key="#Massae" ref="#places/4600"
                                >Fisscal[ia]</placeName></geogName>. In nomine Patris et Filii et
                        Spiritu Sancti. Anno Deo pro[picio ponti]ficatus noster <persName
                            key="#Popes" ref="#people/2144">Alexander</persName> sumo <rs
                            key="#Popes">pontifice</rs> et unive[r]salis pap[e in apostol]ica
                        sacratissima [b]eati Petri apostoli Domini sede anno sesto, <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs>
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/237">Henricus</persName>
                        defunctus, in Ita[lia n]ullus imperatore nondum abemus, die quarto mensis
                        gienuarii, indicione sesta, [in] <rs key="#Vici">vico</rs> qui vocatur
                            <placeName key="#Vici" ref="#places/4619">Ustolatho</placeName>. Petivi
                        [a] te quidem in Dei nomine domnus <persName key="#Priests #Monks #Priors"
                            ref="#people/1599">Gieronimus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs>, <rs key="#Monks">mon(a)h(us)</rs> atque
                            <rs key="#Priors">prior</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Massae #Fundi #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Penalty #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Books #Rent_in_money #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Ma[rie] qui vocatur in <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Pomposea</placeName></orgName>, pro vice ex
                        persona de domnus <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1596"
                            >Maginardo</persName> gracia Dei <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> eiusdem
                        monasterii ordinatore, uti mihi in Dei nomine Urso qui vocatur de Petrus
                        Groso petitore, tam pro [me] quam pro vice ex persona de <persName><name
                                ref="Agneta">Agneta</name></persName> cognus mea seu filiis et
                        heredibus meis, <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">llibellum
                            nomine</rs> [con]cedisti et largisti atque confirmasti [n]obis de rem
                        iuris suprascripto monasterio vestro, idest medietatem in[te]g[ram] de omnes
                        res et portione quan[ta]scumque ovenit per <rs key="#Venditio">cartula
                            conpar[a]cionis</rs> [...] de <persName key="#Venditio"><name
                                ref="Maria de Ingitio">Maria qui vocabatur de
                            Ingizo</name></persName> de <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/594">Ravenn[e]</placeName> a predicto
                        monasterio [v(est)]ro, ipsa [re]s qui est posita in masa Fiscalia et in <rs
                            key="#Fundi">fundo</rs> qui vocatur Capralia, per singulis locis; que
                        omnia cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder"
                            >pr[a]tis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pasculis</rs>, <rs>salectis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">pa[d]ulibus</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscacionibus</rs>, cum ingresu et egresu suo [et] cum omnibus que ad
                        suprascripta medietate de res pertinentibus vel subiacentibus sicut superius
                        legitur. Hec omnia abendum, tenendum, posidendum, laborandum, defensandum et
                        in omnibus meliorandum in annis advenientibus viginti et nove a renovandum
                        salva callciaria domnica dandum llibellum renovemur. Ita sane ut inferamus
                        nobis nostrisque filiis et heredibus vobis vestrisque sucexoribus redere
                        debeamus omnique anno pensione nomine pro suprascripta res <rs
                            key="#Rent_in_money">denaris quatuor monete Veneticorum</rs>, tantum
                        pensio ut dictum est persolvatur. Pro quia esinde acepisti de mani mei
                        suprascripto petitore in manibus tui [s(uprascrip)]to ordinatore callciario
                        nomine, idest <rs key="#Books">llibrum</rs> unum pro in <rs key="#Price"
                            >arientum de denaris [V]eroniense solidos treginta</rs> et per
                        unumquemque solidum denaris duodeci. Maiore quidem domino vel vestra
                        dominacio[n]e cum onore et obediencia susipere debeamus cum fide et puritate
                        sine alico dolo. Si quis ve[ro] pars nostra contra hoc peticione ire
                        temtaverimus ante perfi[n]itum tempus sicut superius legitur det pars parti
                        fidem servandi, ante omnis [lit]is inicium vel interpellacionem, pene nomine
                            <rs key="#Penalty">auri obtimi uncia una</rs> et post [p]ena soluta
                        manead hoc llibellum in sua firmitate. Quos ve[ro] peticione uno pari tinore
                        conscripto <persName key="#Tabellio"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohanne</name></persName> in Dei nomine <rs key="#Tabellio"
                            >tabellio</rs> [sc]ribendum rogavi et subter manu mea propria firmavi et
                        unus al[te]rius nobis pariter iubemus quod consecuti sumus agamus Deum et
                        nobis masimas gracia. Signum + manus suprascripto Urso de Petrus Groso
                        petitore ad omnia suprascripta cui relectum est.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
